latestPosts.caption:
Old-Hollywood grace collides with modern aesthetics as Nargis Fakhri (@nargisfakhri) steps into her most stylish era-where fashion becomes both armour and art. The actor is the epitome of sensuality as she strikes a pose with her big hair and berry red lipstick. A dramatic interplay of sensuality and sophistication, this ensemble from Roseroom by Isha J (@roseroom__official) features a sculpted black bodysuit adorned with delicate lace placements that trace the contours of the body with quiet allure. Paired with a sweeping floor-length jacket, the look transforms into a vision of regal mystery. The jacket’s exaggerated bell sleeves are brought to life with opulent couture hand embroidery—an ode to french architectural motifs and dainty laces, glimmering with antique metallic threads, swarovski, and crystals. Her look has been spruced up with a striking pendant from Diacolor @dia_logues. 

Roseroom By Isha J (@roseroom__official) will be partaking in FDCI (@fdciofficial) Manifest Wedding Weekend on 2-3 August 2025, at Taj Palace, New Delhi.

Our new issue is all about vintage glamour. Bold, fearless and forever stylish. It is a tribute to fashion that never fades.

Gracing our cover is the ever-striking Nargis Fakhri (@nargisfakhri). With her strong presence and effortless charm, she brings our vision to life. From sharp silhouettes to sultry eyes, every frame captures the spirit of old Hollywood with a fresh twist. She doesn’t just wear the clothes. She owns them.

Expect fashion that is dramatic, confident and unapologetically chic. We dive into style stories that honour the past but live in the now. Structured tailoring, rich textures and powerful beauty moments fill these pages.

Nargis Fakhri (@nargisfakhri ) is bringing star power back with ease and attitude. There is a quiet confidence in the way she moves, a sense that she is fully in charge of her next chapter. With Housefull 5 and a Telugu debut alongside Pawan Kalyan, she is not just returning to films but stepping into a space shaped by clarity, self-belief and style.

For the shoot, she wears a silver foil georgette saree by Nidhika Shekhar (@nidhikashekharofficial ). The plain drape and worked palla offer a soft touch of drama, while the one-shoulder padded blouse adds structure and edge. Her look is finished with emerald and diamond earrings from Dillano Jewels. (@dillanojewels )

From island stays and hammam rituals to date tastings and luxury resorts, Bahrain is fast becoming a favourite for Indian destination weddings. 

Just four hours from Delhi, it offers a blend of tradition, modern comfort, and warm hospitality. 

With private villas, beachside vows, and seamless support from Bahrain Tourism, couples can enjoy a stress-free celebration in a setting as rare as the island’s famous pearls.

latestPosts.caption:
Raveena Tandon (@officialraveenatandon) effortlessly blends classic charm with contemporary flair. Her fashion sense is all about elegance with a bold twist—never afraid to experiment, yet always staying true to herself. The actor shares, “If you are aware of what’s going on, how the world is changing around you, and you just go with the flow, the fashion relevance would probably come naturally, because you will wear what is going on around you.”

Shimmering in gold, Raveena wears this dress with a halter-neckline, by Suneet Varma (@suneetvarmaofficial). The bodice of the dress is adorned with intricate sequins and a waist belt. Finally, the long train of the dress adds to visual drama of the look, giving her a luxurious and eye-catching appearance. Her look is further enhanced with a pair of diamond earrings in gold from Shailja’s Fine Jewellery (@shailjas_fine_jewellery).

Suneet Varma and Shailja’s Fine Jewellery will also be part of the FDCI (@fdciofficial) Manifest Wedding Weekend taking place on 2 and 3 August 2025 at Taj Palace in New Delhi.

latestPosts.caption:
Raveena Tandon (@officialraveenatandon) continues to shine as one of Bollywood’s most iconic stars. From ruling the ’90s to redefining elegance today, her screen presence remains unmatched. “My fashion has never been about what is in style at that moment or not in style. I’ve always gone for the evergreen classics. I always wear what I’m comfortable in,” she shares.

She is a vision in this beautiful flowing gown with a plunging neckline and poofy sleeves, from Limerick by Abirr n’ Nanki (@limerickofficial). It has a vibrant multi-coloured print and a pleated texture in shades of blue, green and white. A thigh-slit on the left adds elegance and drama to the look. She finishes her look with a delicate diamond necklace featuring dual crystal pendants by Shailja’s Fine Jewellery (@shailjas_fine_jewellery).
